The spirit prism is an iridescent triangular prism refracting an incoming beam of light into a spectrum. As the item is upgraded, the prism’s output transitions from resembling an orderly spectrum of light to a chaotic explosion of colours with distinct, ribbon-like textures. The item upgrades into Ghost Lens (Farsight), Mana Converter (Mana Into Health) and Witch Clock (CDR)

The savior's mark is a lightly worn piece of red cloth with two vertically stacked white sigils on it. As the item is upgraded, the cloth becomes longer and more sigils are added, eventually gaining a second, rose-coloured cloth tied at one end with its own sigils. The savior's mark upgrades into Physic Crest (Urn) and Soul Prism (Amp+CDR).

The crystal heart is a rough red crystal in an approximately elliptical shape, bulging out further to the viewer’s left than to the right. As it is upgraded, the crystal becomes more refined: remaining rough, but coming to resemble an anatomical depiction of a heart, and gaining a white-pink glow in its centre. The crystal heart upgrades into Sanguine Talisman (Out of Combat Regen) and Crimson Eye (Regen Boost).

The brigandine is an indigo canvas vest and skirt covered in bronze studs. The sigil of the God Beast’s Congregation appears as a faint motif on the torso. It upgrades into Sacred Cuirass (AS Slow + CDR), Feathermail (Lucience), and Frigid Crown (AS Slow + Active Slowing AOE Blast).

Oathplate is a short-sleeved plate chestpiece with a faded coat of arms at its centre. The various seams and accents of the armour appear in the colours of all of the attributes. As the oathplate is upgraded, it gains padding, pauldrons, and the coat of arms is restored. It upgrades into Blighted Cuirass (Damage Aura), Aegis of the Hound (Boost Aura), and Wicked Mail (Damage Return).
